WEBVTT

00:01.369 --> 00:03.769
- Are you okay?
- Yeah, I'm good.

00:03.771 --> 00:05.671
- Richie, what's up?

00:05.673 --> 00:08.507
- If I tell you something,
can you keep me out of it?

00:08.509 --> 00:10.042
- I'm not gonna let anything
happen to you, okay?

00:10.111 --> 00:12.177
- I think I know
where the gun is.
- What're you doing?!

00:12.312 --> 00:14.413
- Sorry, duff. Ds orders.
- Ah!

00:14.482 --> 00:16.247
- Oh. Where'd that come from?

00:16.283 --> 00:17.916
- Union argued that we didn't
have enough

00:17.918 --> 00:20.452
Evidence to let them go,
but that everyone

00:20.488 --> 00:22.988
Would be better served
if we moved them to b&e.

00:22.990 --> 00:25.724
- Alright, just be yourself.
Lean into what's real.

00:25.793 --> 00:27.392
- Like len and the beretta
were real.

00:27.461 --> 00:29.795
- Yeah, actually, they were.

00:29.864 --> 00:31.430
- Kelly marie?
- Len grierson.

00:31.565 --> 00:33.465
- I'm undercover, alright?
- Ditto.

00:33.501 --> 00:35.000
- You're investigating
sons of jupiter?

00:35.002 --> 00:36.901
- Project voltage.
- We want vicky.

00:36.937 --> 00:38.704
A gun she made
nearly killed a cop.

00:38.839 --> 00:41.139
It'll take a little investment
from our part:

00:41.208 --> 00:42.808
$20,000 from the flash fund.

00:42.877 --> 00:45.343
<i> - Marc couldn't be here?</i>
- I can't see a thing.

00:45.345 --> 00:46.845
<i> - You had your chance.</i>
- What are you doing?

00:46.980 --> 00:48.180
- Len's gone. He played us.

00:48.315 --> 00:49.748
- I was thinking about going
to florida

00:49.883 --> 00:51.316
To stay with grandma
for a little bit.

00:51.318 --> 00:53.518
I need a fresh start.
- I love you.

01:07.034 --> 01:09.968
- Obviously, her invisibility
cloak was a metaphor.

01:09.970 --> 01:11.570
- Right.
- Yeah.

01:11.639 --> 01:14.239
Um, hiding her power,
she's concealing herself--

01:14.374 --> 01:15.307
- I see where you're going.

01:15.376 --> 01:16.442
- Yeah?
You know what I'm saying?

01:16.577 --> 01:18.176
- Yeah, yeah, yeah.
- And then this guy,

01:18.312 --> 01:19.711
His big, long sword--
- for sure!

01:19.847 --> 01:21.045
- We obviously know
what that means.

01:21.082 --> 01:22.381
- Well, yeah, it's the whole...
It's the...

01:22.383 --> 01:23.916
Well, I mean,
look at this, sam. You got...

01:24.051 --> 01:26.318
Look what you got going on
in your little area there.

01:26.387 --> 01:27.653
- What? Oh, my god!
- Yeah.

01:27.788 --> 01:28.586
(distant barking)

01:28.622 --> 01:29.721
- Oh, that always happens

01:29.790 --> 01:32.124
When I have double butter.
These are new jeans.

01:32.259 --> 01:33.926
- Well, not anymore.
That's what you get

01:34.061 --> 01:35.928
For hogging all the popcorn,
and keeping it nestled

01:36.063 --> 01:37.862
All up in that area.
That's what's gonna happen.

01:37.898 --> 01:39.064
- Hey, I was clear
from the start.

01:39.199 --> 01:40.398
I do not share my popcorn.

01:40.468 --> 01:42.668
- That's true, that's true.
You've been very clear always.

01:42.803 --> 01:44.936
- Yeah, I'm an open book.
That's part of my charm.

01:44.972 --> 01:46.205
You know what? Go ahead,
ask me anything.

01:46.340 --> 01:47.539
I dare you. I dare you.

01:47.575 --> 01:49.408
- Really? Okay. No, I got ya.
- Okay.

01:49.410 --> 01:51.743
- Uh, guilty musical pleasure?

01:51.812 --> 01:54.613
- Uh... Easy. Styx.
Come sail away.

01:54.615 --> 01:55.881
- I love that song.
- Really?

01:55.883 --> 01:57.015
- Yeah.
- Okay.

01:57.151 --> 01:58.283
- Classic, you know?
- Yeah.

01:58.285 --> 02:00.552
- Dream date.
- Ooh, I know.

02:00.588 --> 02:03.421
The immersive van gogh exhibit
followed by dinner at canoe.

02:03.457 --> 02:05.557
- Oh. Okay.

02:05.593 --> 02:07.626
Um...

02:07.761 --> 02:09.895
Weirdest place
you've ever had sex.

02:10.931 --> 02:13.165
- Canoe. The boat,
not the restaurant.

02:13.234 --> 02:14.832
- I am sensing a theme here.

02:14.869 --> 02:16.434
- It's a bit of one.
- Okay, fair enough.

02:16.504 --> 02:17.435
(rustling)

02:17.471 --> 02:19.905
Sam, look.
No, no. Look, sam, look.

02:20.040 --> 02:21.839
- What?
- What is that?

02:26.947 --> 02:28.513
(whispering): My mother's
in there by herself.

02:28.549 --> 02:30.048
- Okay, hang on.
Let me get my gun.

02:30.050 --> 02:31.649
(distant barking)

02:35.890 --> 02:36.922
(whispering): Mom!
- Quick!

02:36.991 --> 02:39.091
- Are you okay?
(whispering): Oh, you got...

02:39.093 --> 02:42.460
You got your gun. Oh, my god,
- get down, get down, get down!

02:42.496 --> 02:44.196
- Get him, get him!
- What are you doing?

02:44.331 --> 02:46.632
(naz): This is the police!
And for the record, I am armed!

02:46.634 --> 02:48.333
- I'm also the police
and I am also armed!

02:48.468 --> 02:50.368
- Wait, wait, wait!
Mom, don't shoot!

02:51.138 --> 02:52.638
- Elliot! Oh, my god!

02:52.773 --> 02:54.339
- Jesus!
- What are you doing here?

02:54.474 --> 02:55.774
- Sorry. I didn't have my keys.

02:55.843 --> 02:57.475
I-I just didn't want
to wake you up.

02:57.511 --> 02:59.177
- What, so you break in
through my window?!

02:59.180 --> 03:01.079
- Technically,
it's our window, right?

03:01.081 --> 03:03.181
- Oh, kid, you are so lucky

03:03.217 --> 03:06.952
That this ridiculous socialist
state won't let me carry a gun!

03:06.954 --> 03:08.453
- Ow.
- It's the same socialist state

03:08.489 --> 03:10.489
That pays for your bunionectomy,
just to be clear.

03:10.491 --> 03:13.625
- Judy, you got your operation!
- I did, my love!

03:13.627 --> 03:15.694
(laughter)
- you locked up my condo?

03:15.696 --> 03:18.496
- I almost shot your kid.
- I almost shot my kid.

03:18.498 --> 03:20.798
- She's gonna be dead
before the plant.

03:21.501 --> 03:22.767
Seriously.

03:23.804 --> 03:27.973
♪ I hate myself
for loving you ♪

03:27.975 --> 03:32.310
♪ can't break free
from the things that you do ♪

03:32.379 --> 03:34.779
♪ I wanna walk
but I run back to you ♪

03:34.815 --> 03:36.848
- Len, call me. Asshole!

03:38.152 --> 03:39.918
(hiccupping)
- hey.

03:41.055 --> 03:43.121
We need to get a swear jar
for the office?

03:44.158 --> 03:46.458
- Look at you,
all freshly pressed.

03:46.593 --> 03:48.793
Aren't you the perfect picture
of calm.

03:48.829 --> 03:50.462
- Honestly, I've had
enough adrenaline

03:50.531 --> 03:52.264
Coursing through my finely
tuned machine of a body

03:52.333 --> 03:53.865
After nearly killing my son
last night,

03:53.934 --> 03:56.167
But thank you so much
for the compliment.

03:57.804 --> 03:59.471
Hey.
(phone ringing)

03:59.540 --> 04:01.406
You haven't heard anything
from len yet?

04:01.408 --> 04:03.475
- Nope. Two days, nothing.

04:03.477 --> 04:05.176
And until we get those 3d guns,

04:05.178 --> 04:08.213
Richie clarke stays in jail
for shooting a cop. And...

04:08.215 --> 04:10.015
I still don't think
he did it.

04:10.017 --> 04:11.582
- You've been to see richie?

04:11.619 --> 04:13.418
- I tried, but he didn't
want to talk to me.

04:13.420 --> 04:15.754
And why would he? So far,
I have no good news

04:15.823 --> 04:17.289
That'll make him
change his mind.

04:19.226 --> 04:21.360
(hiccupping)
- duff, I need to talk
about the hiccups.

04:21.362 --> 04:23.561
They are a sign of stress.
What you can do--

04:27.635 --> 04:29.367
Hello. Good morning, uh, boss.

04:29.436 --> 04:30.969
- Do not "good morning" me,
detective.

04:31.104 --> 04:34.172
Not unless you've magically
discovered $20,000

04:34.174 --> 04:35.507
And 10 3d guns in your purse!

04:35.509 --> 04:38.343
- Sadly, we have not.
- Duff, get up.

04:38.478 --> 04:39.644
Thanks to you,

04:39.713 --> 04:42.180
Our one lead on the gun
that shot officer beauchamp

04:42.216 --> 04:44.983
Is drifting in the wind
with a rogue agent.

04:45.118 --> 04:47.452
Along with all the evidence
in the case and our flash fund!

04:47.587 --> 04:49.388
- You know what? Kevin looks
really upset, so you might

04:49.523 --> 04:50.988
Want to take it down a notch.
- Ahem!

04:51.025 --> 04:54.092
Find grierson,
bring him in from the cold,

04:54.227 --> 04:56.394
Save this case, save your ass.
(phone vibrating)

04:56.463 --> 04:58.530
Asses. Plural. Both your asses.

04:58.665 --> 05:00.999
So many asses. Hello?

05:03.603 --> 05:04.469
(knocking)

05:04.471 --> 05:06.337
Wazowski, duff, follow me!
- Yep.

05:06.373 --> 05:10.776
- Oh, jesus, mary and joseph.
Look what the cat dragged in.

05:10.778 --> 05:13.412
- What a cute...
That is a dog, right?

05:14.681 --> 05:17.482
I'm len's handler,
sergeant melissa jordan, rcmp.

05:17.518 --> 05:19.217
But you call me mel, or liss--

05:19.286 --> 05:21.886
- I'm not calling you anything
until I understand

05:21.922 --> 05:23.288
How you allowed your agent

05:23.357 --> 05:25.623
To abscond with our guns,
our money,

05:25.693 --> 05:27.626
And our one decent lead
in the shooting

05:27.761 --> 05:29.294
Of a police officer.

05:30.531 --> 05:32.497
- Leonard, you wanna take this?
- Certainly.

05:32.499 --> 05:34.766
I agreed to help out
detectives duff and wazowski

05:34.768 --> 05:36.501
On their gun buy,
but two minutes in,

05:36.537 --> 05:40.304
I saw my target, marc tremblay,
in a car 30 feet away.

05:40.341 --> 05:42.641
Guy followed me.
He's paranoid.

05:42.776 --> 05:44.509
- He's a biker.
Comes with the territory.

05:44.545 --> 05:46.712
(hiccupping)
- so I threw the deal.

05:46.847 --> 05:48.380
Two months in on this play,

05:48.515 --> 05:50.581
I'm almost in with
these sons of jupiter guys,

05:50.617 --> 05:52.317
No easy feat for a black dude.

05:52.452 --> 05:54.586
I needed to look legit.

05:54.588 --> 05:58.055
- So... You handed over 3d guns
to a biker,

05:58.092 --> 06:00.525
Because that's who you want
going through a metal detector?

06:00.660 --> 06:03.462
- I took out the firing pins.
Guns didn't work.

06:03.464 --> 06:05.997
So I figured he might be running
counter-surveillance on me,

06:06.066 --> 06:07.599
So I laid low for a few days.

06:07.734 --> 06:09.934
- And project voltage?
Why use an old name?

06:09.970 --> 06:12.537
- I told len to use it in case
anyone was asking around.

06:12.672 --> 06:14.606
We want to stay completely
under the radar,

06:14.675 --> 06:16.208
Even within our own ranks.

06:16.343 --> 06:18.643
- And you took off
with our money, why?

06:18.645 --> 06:21.079
- Oh, that was
just to look tough.

06:26.854 --> 06:28.953
It's all there.
You can make your arrest.

06:29.022 --> 06:31.088
- What I really care
about right now is finding

06:31.125 --> 06:33.425
That last piece of evidence
against our shooter.

06:33.427 --> 06:35.360
- Maybe it was marc tremblay.
- Mm-mm-mm-mm.

06:35.429 --> 06:36.895
I was with him all that night.

06:36.897 --> 06:38.729
- Correct. All night.
I was listening.

06:38.766 --> 06:40.966
- Well, maybe he gave them
or sold them to someone else.

06:40.968 --> 06:43.168
(hiccupping)
- ahem. Hmm.

06:49.810 --> 06:51.276
Did you try
holding your breath yet?

06:51.278 --> 06:52.844
Biting on a lemon?

06:52.913 --> 06:54.779
- Go to hell, len.

06:54.782 --> 06:57.114
- Want me to fix it?
'cause I will.

06:59.386 --> 07:02.320
- This... Is a huge
case for me.

07:02.356 --> 07:04.055
And you offered to help,

07:04.124 --> 07:05.990
And I vouch for you
like a fool!

07:07.260 --> 07:08.393
And then you go and disappear
on me for three days?

07:08.395 --> 07:09.794
You know, all I know about you

07:09.797 --> 07:12.363
Is that your file says
that you were in rehab,

07:12.399 --> 07:14.465
And that... And that
this project voltage

07:14.501 --> 07:16.267
Doesn't even exist.

07:16.336 --> 07:18.269
- I'm sorry.
(hiccupping)

07:19.806 --> 07:21.239
I... I am...

07:22.676 --> 07:24.342
I should've found
a way to call.

07:24.344 --> 07:26.811
- Yeah. So if you're so sorry,

07:26.814 --> 07:28.814
Find out who marc
sold those guns to.

07:28.949 --> 07:32.284
- I'm meeting up with him now.
I'll see what I can do.

07:32.286 --> 07:33.685
- Good.

07:33.754 --> 07:36.587
It's very cool of you...
Detective.

07:42.496 --> 07:45.062
- Hey, duff, are you in here?

07:48.469 --> 07:49.767
Duff?

07:51.571 --> 07:54.171
(singsong):
I know you're in here!

07:54.208 --> 07:56.574
Duff? Duff...?

07:57.478 --> 07:58.376
(hiccupping)

07:58.445 --> 07:59.644
I know. I know you
don't like talking.

07:59.779 --> 08:01.445
I know that. And I know
that you don't like sharing,

08:01.482 --> 08:02.947
I know you find that hard.

08:04.785 --> 08:06.718
Listen.

08:06.787 --> 08:08.119
Um...

08:10.090 --> 08:11.456
I can only imagine

08:11.525 --> 08:13.992
How weird it is to see len
after all this time.

08:14.127 --> 08:16.595
It's like all the little things
that you know about him,

08:16.730 --> 08:18.997
And all the secrets
that he knows about you.

08:19.066 --> 08:20.899
I bet you guys even have, like,
nicknames for each other,

08:21.034 --> 08:22.400
Like "len the hen" or...

08:22.469 --> 08:24.269
I mean, not that he's
like a chicken.

08:24.338 --> 08:25.670
That one's not right,
I'm so sorry.

08:25.672 --> 08:27.539
But, like, maybe an album.
Like, do you guys got an album

08:27.674 --> 08:28.673
Or a song?

08:28.742 --> 08:30.708
For me, I cannot hear maroon 5's

08:30.710 --> 08:32.877
She will be loved
without thinking about steve.

08:32.946 --> 08:35.012
We were at this criminology
conference in thunder bay,

08:35.148 --> 08:36.848
And then the power went out.
And he was like,

08:36.850 --> 08:38.350
"where's the fuse box?"
I was like, "oh, who cares

08:38.485 --> 08:39.951
About the fuse box?
Look at you in those jeans."

08:40.086 --> 08:41.720
I didn't say that,
but I wish I did, 'cause--

08:41.722 --> 08:43.355
- Really? Maroon 5?

08:43.490 --> 08:44.956
- I know, it's terrible.
But you know what?

08:45.025 --> 08:47.225
Sometimes a song picks you,
you don't pick the song.

08:47.294 --> 08:50.695
- I'm having a really...
Really bad day.

08:51.698 --> 08:55.233
And it's not about boys.
It's about a boy.

08:56.670 --> 08:57.969
- I know.

09:00.840 --> 09:02.373
It's about richard clarke.

09:03.843 --> 09:05.043
Listen.

09:07.714 --> 09:10.114
I promise you. Duff...

09:11.718 --> 09:13.785
I promise we're gonna get there.

09:13.920 --> 09:16.254
- You know... In this job,

09:16.389 --> 09:19.023
You shouldn't make promises,
wazowski.

09:23.863 --> 09:25.663
(siren wailing)

09:26.366 --> 09:28.399
Hey, can I get those, uh,

09:28.435 --> 09:30.402
Richie clarke notes
that you have?

09:30.537 --> 09:33.271
I just want to go over
his files again tonight.

09:33.406 --> 09:35.407
- Yeah, for sure. But, listen.
You know what?

09:35.409 --> 09:37.075
I really think that you need
to take the night off.

09:37.144 --> 09:38.743
Yeah? No, look at me,
look at me.

09:38.878 --> 09:41.479
Beer, bath foam, bed? Come on.
(hiccupping)

09:41.515 --> 09:42.880
Do this for me. Open your mouth,

09:42.882 --> 09:44.282
Pull your tongue out.
Pull it hard.

09:44.351 --> 09:46.084
Give it a try.
- I'm not gonna--

09:46.153 --> 09:48.887
- Just try.
What do you got to lose? Go.

09:49.022 --> 09:50.488
Just do what I say for once.

09:50.524 --> 09:52.090
- Okay.
- There you go.

09:52.159 --> 09:55.326
- Ow. It hurts, though.
(indistinct chattering)

09:56.530 --> 09:57.962
- I come in peace.

10:06.206 --> 10:07.839
Marc tremblay's satellite phone.

10:07.974 --> 10:09.607
He was in my car,
his buzzer was on the dash,

10:09.742 --> 10:11.042
I grabbed it for you.

10:11.044 --> 10:13.845
He thinks he lost it,
he's... Freaking out.

10:13.980 --> 10:15.346
You got three days with it

10:15.349 --> 10:17.448
Before I need
to "find" it for him.

10:18.785 --> 10:20.518
Deal?

10:22.188 --> 10:23.421
- Deal.

10:24.391 --> 10:26.290
- The tongue thing
was pretty cute.

10:30.096 --> 10:32.129
(engine starting, len chuckling)

10:33.733 --> 10:35.133
You're welcome.

10:37.671 --> 10:39.404
- Oh, my god! Oh, my god,

10:39.473 --> 10:41.372
That is marc the shark's
sat phone. Give it here.

10:41.375 --> 10:42.940
I mean please, can I have it?

10:42.976 --> 10:45.309
- Okay, no, stand down.
This is my intel.

10:45.379 --> 10:47.746
- Take the night off and just
let me take it home tonight.

10:47.881 --> 10:49.547
I'm gonna be up late anyway.
I'm having lobster.

10:49.549 --> 10:50.815
I can't sleep on seafood.

10:50.851 --> 10:52.751
It's just a thing. Come on.

10:52.886 --> 10:54.552
Okay, listen.
Come over after dinner,

10:54.554 --> 10:55.487
We can crack it together.

10:55.622 --> 10:58.823
- Pass. But if you find
anything, call me.

10:58.892 --> 11:01.092
- Pinky swear. I promise.
So many promises.

11:01.227 --> 11:02.961
Look at me. Yes!

11:03.096 --> 11:05.029
Up top. Yeah.

11:05.065 --> 11:07.364
- Call me.
- Poof!

11:07.401 --> 11:09.701
By myself. Yes!

11:09.836 --> 11:11.736
(gulls squawking)

11:13.406 --> 11:17.709
- Samantha, can you please
tell me the need for gloves?

11:17.844 --> 11:19.977
If the food isn't safe
for your hands,

11:20.047 --> 11:22.580
How is it safe inside your body?

11:22.649 --> 11:24.449
- It is a mystery.

11:24.518 --> 11:25.717
An even bigger mystery

11:25.786 --> 11:27.384
Is when did you guys
leave florida and why?

11:27.421 --> 11:29.053
I thought you liked it there.

11:29.089 --> 11:30.788
- Yeah, we did.
- We liked it a lot.

11:30.924 --> 11:32.924
Um, I think
we just kind of started--

11:32.993 --> 11:34.993
- It was, like,
we were getting homesick.
- ...Getting homesick.

11:34.995 --> 11:37.328
And we just wanted to, like,
I dunno, take a road trip.

11:37.330 --> 11:38.630
- Road trip. Nice one, my dude.

11:38.765 --> 11:40.664
Nothing like cranking the tunes
on the open road.

11:40.701 --> 11:42.634
- Oh, god.
- Life is a highway!

11:42.769 --> 11:44.268
- Highway!
- Okay...

11:44.337 --> 11:45.903
- No, no, you don't
have to do that.

11:45.905 --> 11:47.972
- Sing the whole song?
- No, you can probably stop.

11:47.974 --> 11:50.241
- Yeah, well, uh...
Here's another mystery.

11:50.376 --> 11:51.876
Why were you with
that detective last night?

11:52.011 --> 11:55.213
- Oh, well, that's, um...

11:55.282 --> 11:57.182
Really, it's because...

11:57.184 --> 11:59.484
Because we were working
on a case, a big case,

11:59.619 --> 12:02.353
And there's just no rest...
Just no rest for the wicked.

12:02.389 --> 12:04.688
- Ha! Samantha, please.
- Please don't.

12:04.725 --> 12:05.924
- You overshare
about everything.

12:06.059 --> 12:07.591
Why not tell the kid the truth?

12:07.627 --> 12:09.860
- Okay. Detective nazeer
